{
    "info": {
        "_postman_id": "c1f7a0b3-f09d-476a-9b48-ef27976e1a47",
        "name": "Heimdall Flight Aggregator: Core Requirements",
        "description": "Comprehensive test suite organized by core functional requirements: aggregation, filtering, ranking, and positional multi-trip validation. Formal contract: docs/openapi.yaml. Local viewers after running `make docs-serve`: http://localhost:8081/swagger-ui.html and http://localhost:8081/redoc.html. The `best_value` ranking uses a weighted score between normalized price and normalized duration. Default weights are `BEST_VALUE_PRICE_WEIGHT=0.6` and `BEST_VALUE_DURATION_WEIGHT=0.4`, which makes the ranking slightly more price-sensitive than duration-sensitive. Concrete mock-data example: QZ7250 has price 485000 and duration 260, GA400 has price 1250000 and duration 110, and JT650 has price 780000 and duration 230. For JT650, minPrice=485000, maxPrice=1250000, minDuration=110, maxDuration=260, so normalizedPrice~=0.386, normalizedDuration=0.8, and the final score~=0.552.",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
